Advance/ Decline Line   A/D   - Define meaning of the word Advance Decline Line
     A technical analysis market timing tool used as an indicator of market movement. The A/D line is derived from the total number of stocks that advanced versus the total number of stocks that declined in price each day on the New York Stock Exchange.
